  "description": "Tax Return Transcript vs Account Transcript: what each shows, when to use each, pitfalls, and how to generate a client-ready report.",
  "content": "<section>\n        <h2 id=\"what-each-shows\" class=\"section-heading\">What Each Transcript Shows</h2>\n        <p class=\"article-text\">These two transcripts get confused constantly because they overlap. They are not the same. The difference is simple: one is designed to track account activity over time, the other is designed to mirror the return as filed.</p>\n        <div class=\"card-glass card-hover p-6 rounded-lg border border-slate-700\">\n        <ul class=\"space-y-2 text-slate-300 text-sm\">\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-purple-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M20 6 9 17l-5-5\"/></svg><span>Account Transcript: the transaction ledger for the year (activity, adjustments, notices).</span></li>\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-purple-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M20 6 9 17l-5-5\"/></svg><span>Return Transcript: the line-item return data as filed (what was reported).</span></li>\n        </ul>\n        </div>\n       </section>\n       <section>\n        <h2 id=\"when-to-use-which\" class=\"section-heading\">When to Use Which</h2>\n        <p class=\"article-text\">Use the Account Transcript for timing, freezes, notices, payments, penalties, and “what happened at the IRS.” Use the Return Transcript when you need what the taxpayer reported, without the entire account history.</p>\n        <div class=\"card-glass card-hover p-6 rounded-lg border border-slate-700\">\n        <ul class=\"space-y-2 text-slate-300 text-sm\">\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-purple-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M20 6 9 17l-5-5\"/></svg><span>Choose Account Transcript for balances, delays, holds, and collections work.</span></li>\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-purple-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M20 6 9 17l-5-5\"/></svg><span>Choose Return Transcript for verifying return data (income, filing status, credits).</span></li>\n        </ul>\n        </div>\n       </section>\n       <section>\n        <h2 id=\"common-pitfalls\" class=\"section-heading\">Common Pitfalls</h2>\n        <div class=\"card-glass p-6 rounded-lg border border-slate-700\">\n         <h3 class=\"font-semibold text-white mb-3\">Common pitfalls</h3>\n         <ul class=\"space-y-2 text-slate-300 text-sm\">\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-rose-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M12 9v4m0 4h.01M10.29 3.86 1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0Z\"/></svg><span>Assuming the Return Transcript will show a refund hold or notice (it often won’t).</span></li>\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-rose-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M12 9v4m0 4h.01M10.29 3.86 1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0Z\"/></svg><span>Skipping the timeline and jumping straight to conclusions.</span></li>\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-rose-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M12 9v4m0 4h.01M10.29 3.86 1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0Z\"/></svg><span>Trying to reconcile payments from a Return Transcript (wrong tool).</span></li>\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-rose-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M12 9v4m0 4h.01M10.29 3.86 1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0Z\"/></svg><span>Using the Account Transcript as a substitute for return line items (slow and noisy).</span></li>\n         </ul>\n        </div>\n       </section>\n       <section>\n        <h2 id=\"cta-parser\" class=\"section-heading\">Generate a Clean Client Report</h2>\n        <p class=\"article-text\">Once you’ve chosen the correct transcript, the next job is communication. Convert it into a report your client can actually understand.</p>\n        <div class=\"mt-6\">\n         <a href=\"/index.html#how-it-works\" class=\"btn-primary text-lg inline-flex items-center justify-center\">Parse Transcript Now</a>\n        </div>\n       </section>",
